  "prompt": "What is a good inpatient drug and alcohol rehab center near Fayette County IN?",
  "response": "When looking for a good inpatient drug and alcohol rehab center near Fayette County, Indiana, it\u2019s important to consider factors such as the types of programs offered, accreditation, staff qualifications, and reviews from past clients. Here are a few reputable options in the surrounding area:\n\n1. **Valley Oaks Health - Residential Treatment**  \n   - **Location:** Lafayette, IN (about 40 miles from Fayette County)  \n   - **Details:** Valley Oaks Health offers residential substance abuse treatment for adults, including dual diagnosis for co-occurring mental health disorders. Their programs focus on individualized care and include therapy, counseling, and aftercare planning.  \n   - **Website:** [valleyoaks.org](https://www.valleyoaks.org)\n\n2. **Fairbanks Hospital**  \n   - **Location:** Indianapolis, IN (about 75 miles from Fayette County)  \n   - **Details:** Fairbanks is a well-known rehab center offering inpatient and outpatient treatment for alcoholism and drug addiction. They provide medically supervised detox, individual and group therapy, and relapse prevention programs.  \n   - **Website:** [fairbankshospital.org](https://www.fairbankshospital.org)\n\n3. **Norton King\u2019s Daughters\u2019 Health - Addiction Treatment Services**  \n   - **Location:** Madison, IN (about 70 miles from Fayette County)  \n   - **Details:** This facility offers inpatient and outpatient addiction treatment services, including detox, counseling, and support groups. They focus on holistic care and long-term recovery.  \n   - **Website:** [nkdh.org](https://www.nkdh.org)\n\n4. **Centerstone**  \n   - **Location:** Columbus, IN (about 40 miles from Fayette County)  \n   - **Details:** Centerstone provides inpatient and outpatient addiction treatment, including detox, therapy, and recovery support. They also specialize in co-occurring mental health disorders.  \n   - **Website:** [centerstone.org](https://www.centerstone.org)\n\n5. **Landmark Recovery**  \n   - **Location:** Carmel, IN (about 80 miles from Fayette County)  \n   - **Details:** Landmark Recovery offers inpatient rehab programs with a focus on evidence-based treatments, including individual therapy, group counseling, and family support.  \n   - **Website:** [landmarkrecovery.com](https://landmarkrecovery.com)\n\n### Tips for Choosing a Rehab Center:\n- **Verify Accreditation:** Look for facilities accredited by organizations like The Joint Commission or CARF.  \n- **Check Insurance Coverage:** Confirm that the facility accepts your insurance or offers payment plans.  \n- **Tour the Facility:** If possible, visit the facility to ensure it meets your needs and feels comfortable.  \n- **Read Reviews:** Look for testimonials or reviews from former clients to gauge the quality of care.\n\nIt\u2019s also a good idea to consult with your healthcare provider or a local addiction specialist for personalized recommendations.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
